ish: {{tt+|tr|ekmek parası}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|food, sustenance, support of life, in general}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|хляб|m}}\n* Estonian: {{t|et|elatis}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|leipä}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|pain|m}}\n* Galician: {{tt+|gl|pan|m}}\n* Georgian: {{tt+|ka|პური}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Brot|n}}\n* Middle English: {{tt|enm|bred}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|pão|m}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|хлеб|m}}\n* Slovak: {{tt+|sk|chlieb}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|riziki|c9|c10}}\n* Turkish:\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|اكمك|tr=ekmek}}\n* Zazaki: {{tt|zza|rızıq|m}}\n}}<!-- close {{multitrans}} -->\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Apache:\n*: Chiricahua: {{t-check|apm|bań}}\n*: Jicarilla: {{t-check|apj|bań}}\n*: Lipan: {{t-check|apl|bań}}\n*: Plains Apache: {{t-check|apk|bań}}\n*: Western Apache: {{t-check|apw|bań}}\n* Breton: {{t+check|br|bara|m}}, {{t-check|br|baraoù}} (1), {{qualifier|collective; rye}} {{t+check|br|segal}} (3)\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[coat]] with [[breadcrumb]]s.\n#: {{co|en|'''breaded''' fish}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* {{l|en|breaded|pos=a}}\n* {{l|en|breading|pos=n}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top-see|to bread|flour|coat}}\n{{multitrans|data=\n* Arabic: {{tt+|ar|خَبَزَ}}\n* Breton: {{tt|br|palañ}}, {{tt|br|paladuriñ}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt|bg|панирам}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|arrebossar}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|panere}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|paneren}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|leivittää}}, {{tt+|fi|paneroida}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|paner}}\n* Galician: {{tt+|gl|empanar}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|panieren}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|paníroz}}, {{tt+|hu|bepaníroz}}\n* Icelandic: {{tt|is|velta}} upp úr {{tt|is|brauðmylsna|alt=brauðmylsnu}}\n* Ido: {{tt+|io|panizar}}\n* Italian: {{tt+|it|impanare}}, {{tt|it|panare}}\n* Persian: {{tt+|fa|نانوایی|tr=nânvâyi}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt|pt|panar}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|панирова́ть|impf|pf}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|sh|поховати}}\n*: Latin: {{tt+|sh|pohovati}}\n* Spanish: {{tt+|es|empanar}}, {{tt+|es|empanizar}}\n* Swahili: {{tt|sw|mkati}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|panera}}, {{tt+|sv|bröa}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt|uk|панірува́ти|impf}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|bột}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|[[טונקען|אײַנטונקען]] [[אין]] [[ברייזל]]}}\n}}<!-- close {{multitrans}} -->\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|en|loaf}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|brede|t=breadth, width, extent|id=breadth}}, from {{inh|en|ang|brǣdu||breadth, width, extent}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*braidį̄||breadth}}. Cognate with {{cog|sco|brede}}, {{m|sco|breid||breadth}}, {{cog|nl|breedte||breadth}}, {{cog|de|Breite||breadth}}, {{cog|sv|bredd||breadth}}, {{cog|is|breidd||breadth}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{lb|en|obsolete|or|UK|_|dialectal|Scotland}} [[breadth|Breadth]].\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* {{l|en|waybread}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\nVariant of {{m|en|braid}}, from {{inh|en|enm|breden}}, from {{inh|en|ang|brēdan}}, {{m|ang|breġdan||to braid}}.\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{l|en|breathe}}, {{l|en|brede}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To form in [[mesh]]es; [[net]].\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# A piece of [[embroidery]]; a [[braid]].\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=abder|Debra|Bader|Aberd|Breda|bared|Debar|beard|arbed|ardeb|Beard|debar}}\n\n{{C|en|Breads|Foods}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|enm|noun|altform=1}}\n\n# {{tlb|enm|Early ME}} {{alt form|enm|bred|t=bread|id=bread}}\n\n==North Frisian==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|frr|briad||Föhr-Amrum}}\n* {{alt|frr|briid||Goesharde}}\n* {{alt|frr|briidj||Mooring}}\n* {{alt|frr|breeđ||Sylt}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|frr|ofs|brēd}}, from {{inh|frr|gmw-pro|*braid}}, from {{inh|frr|gem-pro|*braidaz|t=broad, wide}}.\n\n===Adjective===\n{{head|frr|adjective}}\n\n# {{lb|frr|Heligoland}} [[wide]]\n\n==Old English==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|ang|brēod}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|ang|:inh|gmw-pro:*braud}}\nFrom {{inh|ang|gmw-pro|*braud}}, from {{inh|ang|gem-pro|*braudą}}, whence also {{cog|ofs|brād}} ({{cog|fy|brea}}), {{cog|osx|brōd}} ({{cog|nds-de|Broot}}, {{m|nds-de|Brot}}), {{cog|nl|brood}}, {{cog|goh|brōt}} ({{cog|de|Brot}}), {{cog|non|brauð}} and {{cog|is|brauð}} ({{cog|sv|bröd}}).\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{ang-IPA|brēad}}\n* {{rhymes|ang|æ͜ɑːd|s=1}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ang-noun|n|head=brēad}}\n\n# [[bit]], [[piece]], [[morsel]], [[crumb]]\n# [[#English|bread]] (foodstuff)\n\n====Declension====\n{{ang-decl-noun-z-n|brēad}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{sense|bread}} {{l|ang|hlāf}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|ang|bēobrēad}}\n* {{l|ang|picgbrēad}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desctree|enm|bred}}\n\n{{topics|ang|Foods}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|es|verb form}}\n\n# {{es-verb form of|brear}}"}}